      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of April 30 article in Media Talk about accusations by magazine Radar that Chilean publication plagarized its article Toxic Bachelors; author who previously used title phrase is Danielle Steel</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Because of an editing error, a Media Talk report in Business Day yesterday, about an accusation by the magazine Radar that a Chilean publication had plagiarized its article ''Toxic Bachelors,'' misspelled the surname of a book author who had previously used the title phrase. She is Danielle Steel, not Steele.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
